+ Pages I Have Written
++ [[[SCP-5074]]] -- [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nxH8Bc0cHok Childhoods End, and Bubbles Burst]
It's rough around the edges, but I'm still proud of it. It was my first successful SCP article, and the second one I had posted since middle school in 2018. It's the story of a young chimp's journey through his past to his true purpose, and probably also an expression of my repressed daddy issues.

[[div class="Blockquote"]]
++ [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/aiad-homescreen AIAD]: Limited Memory
+++ With [[*user Placeholder McD]], [[*user Pedagon]], and [[*user Its a Bad Idea]]
++++ 5th place, [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/canon-renaissance-contest 2020 Canon Renaissance Contest]

This is an incomplete list which only includes the parts of the series I wrote or co-wrote. To read the series from the beginning, start from [[[AI Classification Guide]]] by [[*user Placeholder McD]].

* [[[Project RUBY]]]
Drs. Pierre Dagon and Yves Isabi send Mnemosyne, an artificially intelligent conscript they have developed to detect and demystify antimemetic phenomena, on her first mission.
* [[[SCP-5841]]] -- Digital Hydra (with [[*user Placeholder McD]])
A corporate center in Windsor, Ontario, Canada goes dark, and the human MTF sent in to investigate are lost. Can AGI save the day?
* [[[A Symphony of Iron and Steel]]] (with [[*user Its a Bad Idea]])
Mnemosyne and her AI colleagues Glacon and 8-Ball explore an abandoned factory in search of a mysterious fugitive.
* [[[Internet Explorers]]] (with [[*user Pedagon]])
Mnemosyne, Glacon and 8-Ball explore the Internet (circa 1996).
* [[[FRAGMENTED/COMPILED]]] (with Team .AIC)
The epic finale of Limited Memory.
* [[[Isolated, Efficient]]]
An Epilogue.
[[/div]]

Helping write this series was probably the most fun I've ever had on the SCP Wiki and the most fun I ever will have on the SCP Wiki if I continue on the path I'm going on now. I have fond memories of the entire process and I couldn't have joined a better team if I tried.

++ [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/zyn-s-gift-2020 Home is where I want to be]
+++ for Art Exchange 2020

The [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/kiryu-labs-hub Kiryu Labs] crew track an anomaly, doing more good than they realize.

A gift for the incomparable [[*user Zyn]], who I was assigned for my very first art exchange experience. I'm still not sure how that happened. For the first art exchange I participated in on the Wanderers' Library wiki, I also got assigned a master admin: [[*user rumetzen]]. Beginner's luck.

++ [[[SCP-5609]]] -- glow-worm
+++ for [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/jam-con-2021 JamCon 2021]

A gigantic larva orbits the Earth.

I'm very proud of this one, not least because it's the only article of mine I can really call "critically acclaimed" judging by how much unexpected positive attention it received from respected authors.

++ [[[Red, White and Blue Reality]]]
+++ for [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/an-incredibly-importanterest-announcement Creck Fection Contest 2] (unofficial)

In this parody of [[[SCP-3001]]], Dr. Robert Scranton and his good pal Red search for a way out with nothing but the power of their close and intimate friendship, as historians will inevitably wind up calling it.

Loud sound warning. Turn down your volume before clicking on this one.

++ [[[SCP-1699]]] -- Inferior Volcano
+++ a rewrite of the original by pixelatedharmony

A little volcano dreams of mass destruction.

I like to say I hate this one, but looking back -- it was fun to write, it is cute, it was well received. What more can one ask for? Now update your videos, YouTubers. I want more clout.

++ [[[SCP-7222]]] -- Pool Boy
+++ for [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp7000contesthub 7Kcon]

A little pool-cleaning robot dreams of mass sanitation.

This was one of the last things to have been posted for the contest. After going through 2 different ideas, both of which I lacked the confidence to complete in time, I settled for a short and cute story based on an autonomous underwater vacuum cleaner at the swimming pool I worked at that summer paying tribute to some of the other 7Kcon entries I had critiqued and read. I can't believe it's already almost been two years.

++ [[[SCP-6267]]] -- 🟠

A bunch of little orange things dream of mass SCP Foundation Site closure.

This article is based entirely on a pun I thought of while talking to my mom. I love how the -JP branch's [[*user buta_otoko]] managed to [http://scp-jp.wikidot.com/scp-6267 translate it to Japanese] in a way that still made sense.

++ [[[SCP-7524]]] -- Bear Hunt

A little Gamers Against Weed-affiliated hacker dreams of mass advertiser "murder."

Another short thing I made based on a joke. The annoying ad in this one is based on an [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QFn8BO0DhS4 actual series of ads] that annoyed me deeply.

+ [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/anthology-2023-hub ANTHOLOGY 2023]

I don't consider this project "mine," as all I did was prompt the people who actually wrote the stories and made the art. Check out their work! They all did excellently.

